11/12/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska Chief Prosecutor Amor Bukic announced at the weekend that proceedings against ten people charged with war crimes are under way in the entity. He indicated that the recent restructuring of the judiciary and the appointment of new prosecutors has sped up the process significantly.
In other news, the Bosnian Commission for Missing Persons announced on Friday (December 8th) that forensic experts have exhumed the remains of 258 people from a mass grave in the northern area of Brcko. An official says the bodies were those of Muslims and Croats, murdered by Bosnian Serb forces that invaded the area in the early days of the Bosnian conflict. (Dnevni avaz, RTRS, Srna - 10/12/06; DPA, AFP - 08/12/06) 
